genresAdvancedInfo.name: pop boliviano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Pop boliviano is a genre that combines traditional Bolivian music with modern pop elements. The music features the use of traditional instruments such as the charango, quena, and panpipes, along with modern instruments such as guitars and keyboards. The lyrics often focus on social and political issues, as well as love and romance. The music is upbeat and energetic, making it a popular genre for festivals and celebrations.
